<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><description xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" appl="X06/D7D,D7F|X57/D7F|X65/D7D,D7F|X44/D7F|X76/D7D,D7F" id="RDE-000024064" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:description.xsd"><title translate="no">camshaft: check</title><descprolog translate="no"><status name="" translate="no"/><critdates translate="no"><created date="" translate="no"/><revised modified="" translate="no"/></critdates><descmetadata translate="no"><siename translate="no">camshaft: check</siename><sieversion translate="no"/><sietype translate="yes">Description</sietype><sienumber translate="no"/><domain translate="no"/><company translate="no">RENAULT</company></descmetadata></descprolog><descbody translate="no"/><description id="d1e29" translate="no"><title translate="yes">removal preparation operation</title><descbody translate="no"><noteR translate="no" type="warning"><para translate="yes">To avoid all risk of damage to the systems, apply the safety and cleanliness instructions and operation recommendations before carrying out any repair<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3455841"><linkdesc>engine : precautions for the repair</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001545</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></noteR><noteR translate="no" type="caution"><para translate="yes">It is strictly forbidden to apply any pressure to the engine oil sump. Damage to the sump may also damage the engine by:</para><ul translate="no"><li translate="yes">blocking the strainer,</li><li translate="yes">raising the oil level above maximum, with a risk of engine racing.</li></ul></noteR><para translate="yes">Drain the cooling system<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3479881"><linkdesc>coolant circuit assembly : draining - refilling</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-000954</linkvalue></sieref>.</para><para translate="yes">Remove the camshaft<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3456415"><linkdesc>cylinder head : stripping - rebuilding</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-000743</linkvalue></sieref>.</para><para translate="yes">Before any checks:</para><ul translate="no"><li translate="yes">clean the camshaft with<ingredientname translate="yes">surface cleaner</ingredientname><sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3542379"><linkdesc>vehicle : parts and consumables for the repair</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-002445</linkvalue></sieref>and dry using a<?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT80_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">compressed air nozzle</materialname>,</li><li translate="yes">check that the camshaft is not scratched and does not show signs of impact or abnormal wear (replace the camshaft if necessary).</li></ul></descbody></description><description id="d1e71" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Checking the camshaft</title><descbody translate="no"/><description id="d1e75" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Checking the camshaft radial play</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">The radial play (difference between the diameter of the camshaft bearings on the cylinder head and on the camshaft) must be between<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">0.03 and 0.08 mm</value></technicalvalue>.</para></descbody><description id="d1e86" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Checking the camshaft journal diameters</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><figure id="10-02-02-9-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-18" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000002609_LAY-000009725.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000024064-02-02-9-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-18-000002609</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Place the camshaft on two slightly oiled v-blocks.</para><noteR translate="no" type="note"><para translate="yes">Note:</para><para translate="yes">Camshaft bearing No.1 is located on the flywheel end.</para></noteR><para translate="yes">Use a<!--Arbortext, Inc., 1988-2015, v.4002--><?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT47_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">external micrometer</materialname>to measure the outer diameter of every camshaft journal which must be between the following values:</para><table colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1" translate="no"><tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="1" translate="no"><colspec colname="1" colnum="1" colwidth="50%" translate="no"/><colspec colname="2" colnum="2" colwidth="50%" translate="no"/><thead translate="no"><row rowsep="1" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">Number of bearings</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">Camshaft journal diameters</para></entry></row></thead><tbody translate="no"><row rowsep="1" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">No. 5</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes"><technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">41.97 ± 0.01 mm</value></technicalvalue></para></entry></row><row rowsep="1" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">No. 4</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes"><technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">41.57 ± 0.01 mm</value></technicalvalue></para></entry></row><row rowsep="1" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">No. 3</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes"><technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">41.27 ± 0.01 mm</value></technicalvalue></para></entry></row><row rowsep="1" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">No. 2</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes"><technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">40.97 ± 0.01 mm</value></technicalvalue></para></entry></row><row rowsep="0" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">No. 1</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes"><technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">39.97 ± 0.01 mm</value></technicalvalue></para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></descsection></descbody></description></description><description id="d1e169" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Checking the concentricity of the camshaft journals</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e171" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-10X02X02-02X58-1-17.5" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">3</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-10X02X02-02X58-1-17.6" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">2</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-10X02X02-02X58-1-17.7" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">1</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="10-02-02-11-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-19" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000004128_LAY-000009726.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000024064-02-02-11-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-19-000004128</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Place the camshaft on two slightly oiled v-blocks<markref format="dita" href="#d1e169/10-02-02-11-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-19" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">1</markref>.</para><para translate="yes">Fit:</para><ul translate="no"><li translate="yes">the<!--Arbortext, Inc., 1988-2015, v.4002--><?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT45_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">dial gauge support</materialname><markref format="dita" href="#d1e169/10-02-02-11-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-19" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">2</markref>,</li><li translate="yes">the<?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT44_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">Dial gauge</materialname><markref format="dita" href="#d1e169/10-02-02-11-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-19" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">3</markref>.</li></ul><para translate="yes">Fit the sensor of the<?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT44_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">Dial gauge</materialname>against the centre of the camshaft journal mating face.</para><para translate="yes">Set the<?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT44_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">Dial gauge</materialname>to zero.</para><para translate="yes">Rotate the camshaft while avoiding the lubrication holes to check the journal concentricity, which must be less than<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">0.05 mm</value></technicalvalue>.</para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="d1e232" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Checking the height of the cam lobes</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e234" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-10X02X02-02X58-1-17.2" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">H</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="10-02-02-12-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-20" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000004129_LAY-000009727.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000024064-02-02-12-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-20-000004129</illusnum></figure><figure id="10-02-02-8-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-21" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000002608_LAY-000009728.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000024064-02-02-8-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-21-000002608</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Place the camshaft bearings no. 2 and 4 on two slightly oiled v-blocks.</para><para translate="yes">Use a<!--Arbortext, Inc., 1988-2015, v.4002--><?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT47_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">external micrometer</materialname>to measure the height of the cams which must be:</para></descsection><table colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1" translate="no"><tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1" translate="no"><colspec colname="1" colnum="1" colwidth="33.333333333333336%" translate="no"/><colspec colname="2" colnum="2" colwidth="33.333333333333336%" translate="no"/><colspec colname="3" colnum="3" colwidth="33.333333333333336%" translate="no"/><thead translate="no"><row rowsep="1" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">Cam height</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">Inlet</para></entry><entry colname="3" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">Exhaust</para></entry></row></thead><tbody translate="no"><row rowsep="0" translate="no"><entry colname="1" translate="yes"><para translate="yes">All D7</para></entry><entry colname="2" translate="yes"><para translate="yes"><technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">38.62 mm</value></technicalvalue></para></entry><entry colname="3" translate="yes"><para translate="yes"><technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">38.49 mm</value></technicalvalue></para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></descbody></description><description id="d1e291" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Checking the camshaft longitudinal play</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Oil the camshaft.</para><descsection translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e295" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-10X02X02-02X58-1-17.10" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">6</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-10X02X02-02X58-1-17.11" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">5</designation></mark><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-10X02X02-02X58-1-17.12" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">4</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="10-01-98-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-23" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000026154_LAY-000009729.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000024064-01-98-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-23-000026154</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Fit:</para><ul translate="no"><li translate="yes">a metal plate<markref format="dita" href="#d1e291/10-01-98-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-23" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">4</markref>on the cylinder head (example: tool<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">(Mot. 588)</value></technicalvalue>),</li><li translate="yes">the<!--Arbortext, Inc., 1988-2015, v.4002--><?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT45_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">dial gauge support</materialname><markref format="dita" href="#d1e291/10-01-98-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-23" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">5</markref>on the metal plate,</li><li translate="yes">the<?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT44_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">Dial gauge</materialname><markref format="dita" href="#d1e291/10-01-98-repair-10-02-02-02-58-1-17-23" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">6</markref>on the mounting.</li></ul><para translate="yes">Position the dial gauge sensor against the end of the camshaft.</para><para translate="yes">Move the camshaft towards the dial gauge until it hits a stop.</para><para translate="yes">Calibrate the dial gauge to zero.</para><para translate="yes">Move the camshaft towards the side opposite the dial gauge until it hits the other stop.</para><para translate="yes">Check the longitudinal play, which should be between<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">0.07 and 0.15 mm</value></technicalvalue>.</para></descsection><para translate="yes">Remove the camshafts from the cylinder head<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3475275"><linkdesc>camshaft : removal - refitting</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-000143</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descbody></description></description><description id="d1e366" translate="no"><title translate="yes">final operation</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Refit the camshaft<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3456415"><linkdesc>cylinder head : stripping - rebuilding</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-000743</linkvalue></sieref>.</para><para translate="yes">Fill and bleed the cooling system<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3479881"><linkdesc>coolant circuit assembly : draining - refilling</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-000954</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descbody></description></description>